<headline>Hard Freeze Warning issued November 11 at 8:16PM MST until November 12 at 9:00AM MST by NWS Albuquerque</headline>
<description>...HARD FREEZE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM MST SATURDAY...
* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures as low as 22 expected.
* WHERE...Chaves County Plains.
* WHEN...Until 9 AM MST Saturday.
* IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions could kill crops, other
sensitive vegetation and possibly damage unprotected outdoor
plumbing.</description>
<instruction>Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold.</instruction>
